DEFINITIONS

"Software" refers to VoidDream, including all source code, binaries, assets,
themes, icons, documentation, and any associated files in this repository,
in whole or in part, modified or unmodified.

"Author" refers to FemBoyGamerTechGuy, the original creator and sole copyright
holder of the Software, and any successor or assignee of the Author's copyright
who has been publicly designated by the Author in writing.

"You" / "User" refers to any individual or entity other than the Author
accessing, using, copying, modifying, or distributing the Software.

"Personal Use" means use of the Software solely by a single natural person
for their own private, non-commercial purposes on their own devices. Personal
Use does not include use by or on behalf of any company, organisation, group,
or legal entity of any kind, regardless of whether such use is described as
internal, private, or non-commercial.

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software, in whole or in part, that is
intended for or results in commercial advantage, monetary compensation, or
business benefit of any kind, whether direct or indirect.

"Fork" means any copy, clone, or derivative of the Software's repository or
source code, whether or not modifications have been made, and whether stored
locally, hosted privately, or published publicly.

"Redistribution" means sharing, publishing, packaging, uploading, or otherwise
making the Software or any derivative of it available to any third party in any
form, whether source code, compiled binary, or otherwise.

"Permission Grant" means a written authorisation issued by the Author to a
specific individual or entity permitting one or more otherwise-restricted
actions. Every Permission Grant is personal, non-transferable, and subject to
the conditions and limits stated within it and within this license.

"Permitted Party" means any individual or entity that holds a valid, active,
non-revoked Permission Grant from the Author.

