1. PERMISSION GRANTS — GENERAL RULES

All rights not explicitly granted by this license are reserved by the Author.
Any action not permitted by Section 2 (Personal Use) requires a Permission
Grant. The following rules apply to all Permission Grants:

  a) Every Permission Grant is issued in writing by the Author and is specific
     to the individual or entity named within it. It may not be transferred,
     sublicensed, or assigned to any other party without a separate written
     Permission Grant from the Author.

  b) A Permission Grant only authorises the specific actions explicitly stated
     within it. Any action not explicitly listed in the grant remains
     prohibited. Ambiguity in a Permission Grant shall be interpreted narrowly
     and in favour of the Author.

  c) The Author may attach any conditions, time limits, scope restrictions,
     visibility requirements, or other terms to a Permission Grant at the
     time of issuance or at any point thereafter.

  d) The Author may revoke any Permission Grant at any time, for any reason
     or no reason, with or without notice, and regardless of whether the
     Permitted Party has been fully compliant with all terms of this license
     and their Permission Grant. Upon revocation, all rights conferred by
     that grant immediately and permanently cease, and the Permitted Party
     must immediately comply with any instructions issued by the Author.
     Full compliance is not a guarantee of continued permission.

  e) The Author may modify the terms of any Permission Grant at any time,
     including narrowing, expanding, or adding new conditions. The Permitted
     Party must comply with the updated terms from the date they are issued.

  f) No Permission Grant implies any future grant, renewal, or ongoing
     entitlement of any kind.

  g) Any Permission Grant obtained by misrepresentation, fraud, or omission
     of material facts is void from the moment of issuance and confers no
     rights whatsoever.

