4. FORKING

Creating a Fork of the Software is prohibited without a Permission Grant.
Where a Permission Grant authorises forking, the following conditions apply
in addition to any conditions stated in the grant itself:

  a) The Fork must retain this license file in full, without modification,
     in the root of the repository.

  b) The Fork must clearly credit the Author as specified in Section 3.

  c) The Fork must not be relicensed under any other license.

  d) The Fork owner may not remove, alter, or replace this license.

  e) The visibility of the Fork (public or private) is determined solely by
     the Author. If the Permission Grant specifies visibility, the fork owner
     must comply with that specification. If the Permission Grant is silent on
     visibility, the fork must remain private by default until the Author
     explicitly states otherwise in writing. The Author may change the
     visibility requirement at any time and the fork owner must comply
     immediately.

  f) The Author reserves the right to request the takedown, privatisation,
     publication, or deletion of any Fork at any time, for any reason or
     no reason, with or without prior notice, and without providing
     justification. The fork owner must comply immediately upon receiving
     such a request.

  g) This right applies unconditionally — regardless of whether the fork
     owner has fully complied with this license, their Permission Grant,
     or any other condition. Full compliance with all terms does not exempt
     any Fork or its owner from this right, now or at any future point
     in time.

