  c) The Author may impose, modify, or add conditions to a Commercial Use
     Permission Grant at any time, including after the grant has been issued,
     as per Section 1e.

The following are explicitly prohibited without a Permission Grant:

  d) Selling the Software or any derivative of it.

  e) Bundling the Software with a commercial product or service.

  f) Using the Software as part of a paid service or SaaS offering.

  g) Monetising the Software through advertisements, subscriptions, or any
     other revenue model.

The following is permitted without a Permission Grant:

  h) Installing the Software on behalf of a paying customer solely as a
     labour service (e.g. a technician setting up a computer), provided
     that all of the following conditions are met:
       — The Software is installed unmodified.
       — The Software originates directly from the official repository.
       — Any fee charged is solely for the installer's labour and is
         reasonable in relation to the labour performed. No fee may be
         charged specifically for the Software itself or framed as payment
         for access to the Software.
